/* README */
pl0_rb is a ruby version of PL0 designed by Dr.Worth
written in pascal.
you see 4 ruby files and some test programs here.
1. pl1.rb
2. inter1.rb
3. mysym2.rb
4. error.rb
usage:
1. pull one test file from tes_prog and put it in 
   a same level of pl1.rb
2. $ ./pl1.rb if
3. you will see if.cod file generated.
4. $ ./inter1.rb if.cod
5. in default you see 3 prints, 1st is intermediate file,
   2nd is same but all in numbers, then 3rd is first 24 stack
   is in view, for we can see whats up.
Look at it, Expand it, Modify it, As you like.
pl0_rb is LEMA.

